<div id="review_497153177" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/497153177" />
    <a title="Rusalka" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6163718-rusalka"><img alt="Rusalka" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591511894p2/6163718.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/497153177?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rusalka" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rusalka" href="/user/show/6163718-rusalka">Rusalka</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780790008691" href="/book/show/949041.The_Whale_Rider">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Rusalka by: </span>
      Will
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=kiwi">kiwi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=around-the-world">around-the-world</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=pacific">pacific</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=own">own</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=rl-friends-recomendations">rl-friends-recomendations</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=tourist-atw">tourist-atw</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=magic-realism">magic-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6163718-rusalka?shelf=random-atw-challenge-2020">random-atw-challenge-2020</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer497153177" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13481077858171679968">I still love Witi Ihimaera&apos;s writing. I spend so much of his books committing Māori words to memory, in a vain attempt (I suck at languages) to be able to remember and use words after I finish reading. <br/><br/>I hate though books with ingrained cultural misogyny and an exceptional girl having to spend all her time &quot;proving&quot; she is worthy, let alone better than the men and boys in the novel due to this. I understand it as a trope. I understand it as a realistic thing that happens All. The. Fricking. Time</span>
  <span id="freeText13481077858171679968" style="display:none">I still love Witi Ihimaera's writing. I spend so much of his books committing Māori words to memory, in a vain attempt (I suck at languages) to be able to remember and use words after I finish reading. <br /><br />I hate though books with ingrained cultural misogyny and an exceptional girl having to spend all her time "proving" she is worthy, let alone better than the men and boys in the novel due to this. I understand it as a trope. I understand it as a realistic thing that happens All. The. Fricking. Time. <br /><br />I'm just tired. I'm tired of 2020 and it's made me tired of this kind of irrelevant crap that still carries on despite decades of movements trying to get over all of this. The story itself is great, and I'd read the back of a cereal box if he wrote it. Kahu just deserves a better world and therefore I can't love it as a whole as I was so annoyed all the time. She deserves a place where she is valued for who she is, not her bits.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13481077858171679968" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

