<span id="freeTextContainer7187793630341018809">Kahu is the eldest great-grandchild of Kori, the chief of the Maori in Whangara, New Zealand. Unfortunately, Kahu is a girl and therefore Kori has no interest in her because he is only focused on finding the next leader of the tribe. Kahu showers Kori with love and admiration despite the fact that he continuously dismisses her and he continues his classes for the the males in the tribe and searches for the &quot;one.&quot; <br/><br/>This is a heartwarming story of a detrmined little girl and her quest to find her w</span>
  <span id="freeText7187793630341018809" style="display:none">Kahu is the eldest great-grandchild of Kori, the chief of the Maori in Whangara, New Zealand. Unfortunately, Kahu is a girl and therefore Kori has no interest in her because he is only focused on finding the next leader of the tribe. Kahu showers Kori with love and admiration despite the fact that he continuously dismisses her and he continues his classes for the the males in the tribe and searches for the "one." <br /><br />This is a heartwarming story of a detrmined little girl and her quest to find her way into her great-grandfather's heart. The combination of Maori legend and the present day is amazing and makes for an interesting and good novel.</span>
